Hello Rafaella,
Please see below [in blue] my responses to the questions in your email belo=
w dated September 6, 2025.
Please also find attached a copy of the =E2=80=98Material Damage Report=E2=
=80=99 & the =E2=80=98Scope of Works=E2=80=99 which relates to the damage r=
eport.
I have done my best to answer the specific questions that you have raised. =
My general response to your enquiries is summarised as follows:


  1.  All material and documentation of any form, in respect of your claim,=
 is discoverable and is available to be provided to you. This will remain y=
our enduring right through-out the claim process.
  2.  I will need to work closely with your Claim Manager to ensure the inf=
ormation that you are requesting is provided to you in a timely manner. I a=
m wiling to assist the Claims Manager in this respect.
  3.  All aspects of potential damage which you are seeking to receive assu=
rances on can be responded to on an individual basis. I am unable to provid=
e those responses to you in this email, as I will require consultation and =
input from the relevant specialists and consultants.

I think the most constructive next step would be for me to schedule a meeti=
ng with the key stakeholders within Tower Insurance and following that prov=
ide you with the clarification that you have requested.
Please allow me to schedule a meeting with my colleagues and take the time =
required to provide you with a considered and comprehensive response.
Best Regards,
Grant.

